🌍 How to Install Nexus Globally
To use Nexus as a generic tool in any workspace on your machine, follow these steps:

Open your terminal in the sdlc-terminal root directory.
Run the global installation command:
bash
npm install -g .
Verify the installation: You can now run nexus from any other folder on your computer:
bash
nexus terminal
Note: When running in a new workspace, ensure you have your .env file (or environment variables) configured for Azure OpenAI so the AI features can initialize.

Your enterprise-grade SDLC orchestrator is now live and ready to be used as a global productivity tool!